100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 13, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing measures to prevent future conflicts in Europe. In the United States, the Supreme Court upheld the constitutionality of the federal income tax, a ruling that solidifies government revenue amid ongoing debates on fiscal policy. Meanwhile, in Mexico, President Plutarco Elías Calles faced increasing opposition as tensions rose over church-state relations, signaling potential unrest.
